identity.name: Code
identity.description: The code (used as the code in the resource instance). If the code is in italics, this indicates that the code is not selectable ('Abstract')

identity.name: Display
identity.description: The display (used in the display element of a Coding). If there is no display, implementers should not simply display the code, but map the concept into their application

identity.name: Definition
identity.description: An explanation of the meaning of the concept

values: The resource containing this link must no longer be used. The link points forward to another resource that must be used in lieu of the resource that contains this link.

The resource containing this link is the current active record. The link points back to an inactive patient resource that has been merged into this resource, and should be consulted to retrieve additional referenced information.

The resource containing this link is in use and valid but not considered the main source of information about a resource. The link points forward to another resource that should be consulted to retrieve additional resource information.

The resource containing this link is in use and valid, but points to another resource that is known to contain data about the same object. Data in this resource might overlap or contradict information found in the other resource. This link does not indicate any relative importance of the resources concerned, and both should be regarded as equally valid.
